==Chinese==
===Mandarin===
[[Pinyin]]: mŭdān huā xià sĭ, zuòguĭ yĕ fēngliú.
===Etymology===
Literally: If I should die beneath a [[Peony]] flower, I will still be amorous as a ghost.
*Note: [[Peony]] flower is a metaphor for a beautiful woman.

===Proverb===
'''[[牡丹]][[花]][[下]][[死]]，[[做鬼]][[也]][[風流]]'''
# If I die under a skirt, I can still flirt as a ghost.<sup>1</sup>
# If my body should perish, girls I'll still cherish.<sup>2</sup>
===Alternative forms===
[[牡丹花下死，做鬼也风流]] ([[Simplified Chinese]])

===Footnotes===
====Notes====
*source of both footnotes 1 and 2: ''[[w:House of Flying Daggers|House of Flying Daggers]]'' (Title 01 Chapter 06 H 0 M 22 S 53), said by [[w:Takeshi Kaneshiro|Takeshi Kaneshiro]]'s character.  In the movie, he actually says: [[寧]][[在]][[花]][[下]][[死]]，[[做鬼]][[也]][[風流]] (Literally: "If I would rather die under a flower; I will still be amorous as a ghost").
<sup>1</sup>From the English subtitles in the Movie <br>
<sup>2</sup>From the dubbed English track in the Movie

